{
  "page": "Violande",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the septa, see <a href=\"/index.php/Violante\" title=\"Violante\">Violante</a>.</div>\n<p>The <i><b>Violande</b></i> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Bravos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bravos\">Bravosi</a> merchantman during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Violande&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <i>Violande</i> sailed Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and her party to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> after she fled <a href=\"/index.php/King%E2%80%99s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King’s Landing\">King’s Landing</a>. Having no coin Rhaenyra was forced to sell her crown to pay for passage.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the voyage strong winds pushed the <i>Violande</i> closer to the shores of <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a> than the queen would have liked. It passed three times within hailing distance of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>'s warships, but Rhaenyra took care to keep out of sight.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <i>Violande</i> put to harbor below the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonmont\" title=\"Dragonmont\">Dragonmont</a> on the eventide. The queen disembarked with her son, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon the Younger</a>, her ladies, and three Queensguard knights, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harrold_Darke\" title=\"Harrold Darke\">Harrold Darke</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Adrian_Redfort\" title=\"Adrian Redfort\">Adrian Redfort</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Loreth_Lansdale\" title=\"Loreth Lansdale\">Loreth Lansdale</a>. At the port she found a forty strong escort commanded by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Alfred_Broome\" title=\"Alfred Broome\">Alfred Broome</a> waiting for her, completing the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Fall of Dragonstone\">fall of Dragonstone</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Violande&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Overthrown.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403235146\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.030 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.064 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 323/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8674/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1528/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 717/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1520/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.020/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.64 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   56.119      1 -total\n 65.45%   36.732      1 Template:Italic_title\n 15.98%    8.966      3 Template:Ref\n 13.83%    7.763      1 Template:For\n 10.77%    6.043      3 Template:Ref/core\n  3.92%    2.200      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:15914-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403235146 and revision id 301181\n -->\n",
